# Starfinder DM Tool - Active Encounter Check

Whenever requested to change an element, component, style, or logic on a static page (e.g., Creature Detail, Player Detail, Items, etc.), you MUST verify if this change impacts the Active Encounter (`EncounterActiveOverlay.jsx` / `ActiveEncounter.jsx` / `EncounterInitiativeList.jsx`). 

The Active Encounter aggregates components from across the application and uses mathematical wrappers like `getModifiedStat` to handle live condition tracking. 

If there is crossover, you must explicitly ask the user to confirm whether the Active Encounter component also needs updating to match or be re-integrated.
